00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:54,475
that Weber is now removing
from the lead containment unit.

247
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:57,915
Very good, Weber.

248
00:20:58,040 --> 00:21:00,190
Then you place
the radioactive isotope...

249
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:02,754
carefully behind
the sliding shutter.

250
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:07,029
You see, the sliding shutter
works just like a camera.

251
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:08,912
It regulates the flow
of gamma radiation.

252
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:13,073
Instead of billions of random particles,
you have a precise stream of energy.

253
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:18,558
Now we carefully place
the sliding shutter mechanism...

254
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:21,114
underneath the flubber.

255
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:23,629
And l`m burning up in here!
Weebo!

256
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:25,557
Over here.

257
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:28,592
The gamma radiation triggers a
metastable decay in the flubber itself.

258
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:30,511
- Right.
- Which releases enormous
quantities of energy,

259
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,431
- and that`s what propels the flubber.
- Of course.

260
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:34,590
Now doing it this way,
I believe, is a lot more scientific...

261
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,517
than dropping it
or kicking it...

262
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:38,596
or bombarding it
with light bulb photon flashes.

263
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:42,190
- Absolutely.
- I believe...

264
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:44,919
by controlling
the gamma radiation flux,

265
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:49,630
we can control the movement
of the flubber itself.

266
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:52,274
- Cross your fingers, Weebo.
- Here`s hoping!
- Good luck.

267
00:21:57,120 --> 00:22:00,271
Oh, yes!

268
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,595
It works!

269
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:08,317
Descent, gradually.

270
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:14,038
Back up again. Yeah!

271
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:21,239
My wedding. Oh!

272
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:23,311
- I`ve gotta go, Weebo.
- But you haven`t finished
the experiment yet.

273
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:26,159
You`re just getting started.
You can`t just stop in the middle.

274
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:28,754
The wedding. Oh, I can`t
miss this one, Weebo.

275
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,831
I`m aware of the time.
Thank you.

276
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:33,480
But your days are wrong.
I`m getting married Friday, 6:30 p.m.

277
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:37,070
- No. No, you`re not.
- Why not?

278
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:40,038
Because you`re not
getting married, Phillip.

279
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:42,993
- Yes, I am.
- You missed the wedding.

280
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:46,356
It`s 6:30 in the morning.

281
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:48,755
No. No.

282
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:51,189
Yes. I`m sorry.

283
00:22:56,760 --> 00:22:59,149
- It is?
- Yeah.

284
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:03,829
Sara.

285
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:32,071
Sara?

286
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,239
You have a lot of nerve
to show your face around here...

287
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:41,079
after what you did to me
last night.

288
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:43,799
Will you please let me explain?

289
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:48,914
No. There`s nothing to explain.
You weren`t there.

290
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,639
For the third time you left me
standing at the altar.

291
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:56,274
I`m sorry with all my heart.

292
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:58,430
But please listen to me, Sara.
Please. You know me.

293
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:01,233
You know how sometimes I can get
really fixated on an idea?

294
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:03,151
- I don`t want to hear it.
- Sara, you`ve got to hear it.

295
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:08,268
Sara, this is the reason
I didn`t make it last night.

296
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,480
It`s flubber.

297
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:15,034
Flubber! lt`s a metastable
compound, Sara.

298
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:17,594
In layman`s terms, if you apply
a small amount of energy,

299
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:21,237
it liberates an enormous
quantity of energy.

300
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:23,157
But the total effect
is transient, Sara.

301
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:27,114
The moment you stop applying energy,
it returns to a quasi-plasmoid state.

302
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:30,829
- Isn`t it remarkable, Sara?
- What`s remarkable, Phillip,

303
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:32,757
is that I ever fell
in love with you.

304
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:35,952
You broke my heart...

305
00:24:36,040 --> 00:24:37,871
