I`m on, uh, academic probation.

327
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:20,513
- How did this happen?
- I`m supposed to get A`s.

328
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:23,393
- At least, that`s what I was told.
- The only reason...

329
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:25,829
I loaned this "jerknut"
college money...

330
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:30,277
was so he could get straight A`s
and go to Harvard Business School.

331
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,755
- This isn`t supposed to happen.
- Yes, sir.

332
00:26:32,840 --> 00:26:36,150
We talked to the, uh, that Brainard guy,
the chemistry professor.

333
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:38,840
Now, either he did not
understand us, or he forgot.

334
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:41,315
The-The boy knew we were having
persuasion problems, sir.

335
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:45,274
I have a science requirement,
you morons!

336
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:47,391
Quiet.

337
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:49,556
We`ll have to get the "F"
changed to an "A."

338
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:54,675
It won`t work. This guy? He
doesn`t live in the real world.

339
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:57,109
- He has principles.
- Get something on him...

340
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:59,993
that we can use to force him
to change the kid`s grade.

341
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:03,556
When a man says he has
principles, what he means is...

342
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:06,240
