00:59:50,720 --> 00:59:53,234
`cause I don`t get
any more chances with her.

737
00:59:53,360 --> 00:59:57,399
That`s not true. There`s always another
chance. I mean, you never know, right?

738
00:59:57,520 --> 00:59:59,431
Probably just as well
that it`s over.

739
00:59:59,520 --> 01:00:02,956
- Why?
- She has to move on.

740
01:00:03,040 --> 01:00:05,600
- Oh.
- I`m not right for her.

741
01:00:05,720 --> 01:00:07,790
- But you knew that, didn`t you, Weebo?
- Huh?

742
01:00:07,920 --> 01:00:10,514
You never wanted me
to marry her.

743
01:00:11,800 --> 01:00:15,509
Well, you were right.
I wasn`t right for her.

744
01:00:15,640 --> 01:00:18,518
You`re the one for me, Weebo.

745
01:00:18,600 --> 01:00:20,511
Just the two of us.

746
01:00:21,600 --> 01:00:23,795
And flubber makes three.

747
01:00:25,320 --> 01:00:27,914
- Good night, Weeb.
- Good night.

748
01:00:29,520 --> 01:00:31,317
Uh, Professor--

749
01:00:36,640 --> 01:00:38,596
And this is the God`s truth:

750
01:00:38,720 --> 01:00:41,359
I want him to have
what he wants,

751
01:00:41,440 --> 01:00:44,079
even if it means you
instead of me.

752
01:01:04,360 --> 01:01:06,191
Ooh!

753
01:01:17,520 --> 01:01:21,069
Sara? Sara, it`s me.

754
01:01:21,200 --> 01:01:23,953
- Weebo?
- May I come in?

755
01:01:24,040 --> 01:01:26,508
Oh, l`m sorry
to wake you like this,

756
01:01:26,640 --> 01:01:30,633
but I can`t ring the doorbell.

757
01:01:30,720 --> 01:01:33,075
- Is everything okay with Phillip?
- Oh, yeah.

758
01:01:33,200 --> 01:01:35,839
It`s not
a conventional emergency.

759
01:01:35,960 --> 01:01:39,635
Oh, Phillip would be very angry
if he knew I left,

760
01:01:39,760 --> 01:01:41,955
but I have
to show you something.

761
01:01:42,080 --> 01:01:44,435
Do you have a minute?

762
01:01:44,520 --> 01:01:46,476
Listen.

763
01:01:46,560 --> 01:01:50,519
I know I love her, Weebo.

764
01:01:50,640 --> 01:01:54,030
Every neuron in my limbic system
is saturated with phenylethylamine.

765
01:01:54,160 --> 01:01:57,789
That triggers euphoria,
elation, exhilaration.

766
01:01:57,920 --> 01:02:00,992
Truth is, Weebo, l`m not absent-minded
because l`m selfish...

767
01:02:01,120 --> 01:02:04,669
or crazy or-- or inconsiderate.

768
01:02:06,080 --> 01:02:08,913
I`m absent-minded because l`m
in love with Sara.

769
01:02:09,040 --> 01:02:10,837
Oh.

770
01:02:16,160 --> 01:02:18,754
And this will be
our little secret.

771
01:02:30,400 --> 01:02:32,914
Phillip.

772
01:02:37,600 --> 01:02:39,431
Oh.

773
01:02:41,200 --> 01:02:44,078
- Sara?
- Uh-huh.

774
01:03:03,800 --> 01:03:06,951
This is it.
This is the solution.

775
01:03:07,040 --> 01:03:10,271
This is how we save the school.

776
01:03:10,400 --> 01:03:13,119
That`s what l`ve been saying.
Flubber.

777
01:03:13,240 --> 01:03:15,435
- You saw what it did at the game.
- Yes.

778
01:03:15,520 --> 01:03:17,351
Imagine the line of shoes
we could develop.

779
01:03:17,440 --> 01:03:19,556
Oh, no, no, no, Phillip,
not shoes.

780
01:03:19,680 --> 01:03:21,636
No. Look.

781
01:03:21,760 --> 01:03:24,115
This. Flight.

782
01:03:25,280 --> 01:03:26,554
- Flight?
- Yes.

783
01:03:26,680 --> 01:03:28,750
- Oh, of course.
- A-Air travel.

784
01:03:28,840 --> 01:03:30,751
Oh, Sara! Air travel.

785
01:03:30,880 --> 01:03:32,598
- Yes.
- Oh.

786
01:03:32,720 --> 01:03:36,110
- We`d better sell this
to a car company.
- Oh, Phillip.

787
01:03:51,240 --> 01:03:53,629
- Hey!
- Dr Reynolds.

788
01:03:53,760 --> 01:03:57,150
Professor. It`s a pleasure
to finally meet you.

789
01:03:58,600 --> 01:04:00,909
I believe you know my son.

790
01:04:01,000 --> 01:04:03,798
He used to play basketball
for Medfield.

791
01:04:05,120 --> 01:04:07,588
Lovely old car.

792
01:04:07,680 --> 01:04:10,752
Mind if I take a look
under the hood?

793
01:04:10,880 --> 01:04:13,348
Yes, I do.

794
01:04:13,440 --> 01:04:17,956
And I don`t appreciate you gentlemen
letting yourselves onto my property.

795
01:04:18,080 --> 01:04:22,119
I expected something
more complex.

796
01:04:22,240 --> 01:04:25,835
There`s a lot of money
in your discovery.

797
01:04:25,920 --> 01:04:28,115
Perhaps we could make a deal.

798
01:04:29,840 --> 01:04:32,832
Any discovery I make will belong
to Medfield College.

799
01:04:32,960 --> 01:04:35,918
At the end of the term there isn`t
going to be a Medfield College.

800
01:04:36,000 --> 01:04:39,549
- We`ll see about that.
- You could make a lot of money.

801
01:04:41,680 --> 01:04:45,468
If we were interested in making money,
we wouldn`t have become teachers.

802
01:04:45,600 --> 01:04:48,273
You think you`ll be able to sell
it for what you owe me...

803
01:04:48,360 --> 01:04:50,237
by the end of the term?

804
01:04:50,360 --> 01:04:52,271
We-- We will.

805
01:04:52,400 --> 01:04:56,075
I`ll forget the debt right now.

806
01:04:56,160 --> 01:04:59,152
No, l`m not selling.

807
01:04:59,280 --> 01:05:02,670
When I leave,
I take my offer with me.

808
01:05:02,800 --> 01:05:05,837
We understand.

809
01:05:05,920 --> 01:05:07,751
Good luck.

810
01:05:10,920 --> 01:05:13,036
Come on.

811
01:05:13,120 --> 01:05:14,951
Watch your back, smart guy.

812
01:05:15,040 --> 01:05:17,110
Bad move, Professor.

813
01:05:29,600 --> 01:05:31,431
Good morning!

814
01:05:34,800 --> 01:05:36,756
Pardon me, Mr Seldon.

815
01:05:36,880 --> 01:05:39,633
Are you interested in seeing
a Phillip Brainard?

816
01:05:39,720 --> 01:05:44,157
- Who?
- He`s the college professor
you spoke to on the sixth...

817
01:05:44,280 --> 01:05:46,271
about a brand-new car design.

818
01:05:46,400 --> 01:05:49,472
Tell him l`m busy.
Thank him for the interest.

819
01:05:49,600 --> 01:05:52,592
- And send him a hat.
- Well, he`s here.

820
01:05:52,720 --> 01:05:56,235
He`s right outside.

821
01:06:13,560 --> 01:06:16,438
It`s one of the rarest looks
in watches you can actually own.

822
01:06:16,520 --> 01:06:18,715
This watch we have here
is called the scarab.

823
01:06:18,840 --> 01:06:20,671
It has Swiss--

824
01:06:22,720 --> 01:06:24,995
Good night, Weber.

825
01:06:40,160 --> 01:06:42,355
What?

826
01:07:05,160 --> 01:07:07,151
One goon.

827
01:07:08,920 --> 01:07:11,639
Two goons.

828
01:07:34,080 --> 01:07:35,957
- Hey.
- What?

829
01:07:36,040 --> 01:07:39,077
- I think I found it.
- You found it, all right!

830
01:07:45,600 --> 01:07:48,910
- What was that?
- Take two.

831
01:08:05,840 --> 01:08:08,752
Knock, knock!

832
01:08:22,000 --> 01:08:23,797
Kiss me, big boy!

833
01:08:37,200 --> 01:08:39,953
Did you get it?

834
01:08:40,080 --> 01:08:41,877
Yeah.

835
01:08:53,400 --> 01:08:56,597
Oh, l-l`ve never seen
so many zeroes.

836
01:08:56,720 --> 01:08:59,632
When they saw us flying,
they couldn`t wait to write the cheque.

837
01:08:59,720 --> 01:09:02,280
This will save the school,
Phillip.

838
01:09:18,440 --> 01:09:20,271
Weebo?

839
01:09:25,280 --> 01:09:27,111
Weebo?

840
01:09:34,440 --> 01:09:37,034
They took the flubber.

841
01:09:37,120 --> 01:09:39,554
Weebo?

842
01:09:47,560 --> 01:09:49,755
- Weeb--
- Oh.

843
01:09:49,880 --> 01:09:52,440
Um, sh-she`s leaking
battery fluid.

844
01:09:54,080 --> 01:09:56,514
Weebo, it`s me.

845
01:10:00,120 --> 01:10:03,874
Do you have signal?
Do you have audio signal?

846
01:10:04,000 --> 01:10:06,833
Tracking. It`s me.
Professor Brainard.

847
01:10:06,920 --> 01:10:09,912
Focus. Weebo?

848
01:10:10,040 --> 01:10:12,429
Can you see me?

849
01:10:13,920 --> 01:10:16,673
She sees me.

850
01:10:18,640 --> 01:10:21,108
Weebo.

851
01:10:21,240 --> 01:10:24,357
It`s all right. I`ve-l`ve-- I need
to get some sort of extension cord,

852
01:10:24,480 --> 01:10:27,040
something so I can recharge her.

853
01:10:27,160 --> 01:10:29,549
I`ve gotta-- I`ve gotta
download her, quick.

854
01:10:29,680 --> 01:10:31,636
Weebo?

855
01:10:31,720 --> 01:10:33,995
It`s all right. It`s okay.

856
01:10:34,080 --> 01:10:37,390
Weebo, can you hear me?

857
01:10:41,160 --> 01:10:43,754
It`s gonna be all right.

858
01:10:43,840 --> 01:10:47,628
It`s like that time you ran into
the wall when I first made you.

859
01:10:47,720 --> 01:10:50,188
We`ll get you upstairs,
onto AC and--

860
01:10:52,440 --> 01:10:54,510
She`s-She`s losing--

861
01:10:54,600 --> 01:10:58,991
She`s losing power.
It`s okay. It`s all right.

862
01:10:59,120 --> 01:11:01,236
We just gotta get you
to the docking station...

863
01:11:01,360 --> 01:11:03,954
till I can make repairs.

864
01:11:11,200 --> 01:11:12,997
Weebo?

865
01:11:17,200 --> 01:11:19,475
Goodbye, my friend.

866
01:11:28,160 --> 01:11:30,993
Gone. I have no idea what--

867
01:11:32,280 --> 01:11:34,077
Goodbye.

868
01:11:55,600 --> 01:11:57,716
I don`t know what
to do with her.

869
01:12:00,480 --> 01:12:03,756
What happens to the soul
of a machine, Sara?

870
01:12:07,640 --> 01:12:10,074
Can you fix her?

871
01:12:10,200 --> 01:12:12,634
I can make repairs,

872
01:12:12,760 --> 01:12:16,070
but I can never bring back
the life it was she had.

873
01:12:16,160 --> 01:12:18,833
That`s gone.

874
01:12:18,960 --> 01:12:22,396
I never knew what it was to begin with.
It was some sort of glorious accident.

875
01:12:22,520 --> 01:12:27,310
I kept trying to recreate it
and isolate it and find out what it was.

876
01:12:27,400 --> 01:12:29,709
I never could.

877
01:12:31,280 --> 01:12:34,113
What was that word
she was displaying...

878
01:12:34,240 --> 01:12:36,800
on her screen at the end?

879
01:12:36,920 --> 01:12:39,388
Probably a file name.

880
01:12:39,520 --> 01:12:41,590
Why was she displaying it?

881
01:12:41,720 --> 01:12:45,110
She was damaged-- It`s, you know--
download-- random piece of information.

882
01:12:45,240 --> 01:12:47,310
- I don`t know.
- What was that word?

883
01:12:49,120 --> 01:12:51,475
Oh, can you remember?

884
01:12:51,600 --> 01:12:53,989
No, l--

885
01:12:54,080 --> 01:12:56,913
- Try.
- I am.

886
01:13:02,120 --> 01:13:04,111
It began with "S."

887
01:13:11,400 --> 01:13:15,439
Hello, Phillip. It`s me. Weebo.

888
01:13:15,520 --> 01:13:18,080
If I was human, that is.

889
01:13:18,200 --> 01:13:21,829
If you`re watching this,
l`m no longer here.

890
01:13:23,360 --> 01:13:26,477
I hope my demise didn`t
cause you any undue distress.

891
01:13:27,800 --> 01:13:30,030
Phillip,

892
01:13:30,120 --> 01:13:33,874
a full and complete design
of me is in this file.

893
01:13:34,000 --> 01:13:37,231
You didn`t forget it.
I never showed it to you.

894
01:13:38,440 --> 01:13:40,954
I`ve made a few changes.

895
01:13:41,080 --> 01:13:43,833
I`ve removed a few
of my flaws...

896
01:13:45,200 --> 01:13:47,589
and added a little of you.

897
01:13:49,960 --> 01:13:53,077
I hope you that
you can love my daughter...

898
01:13:53,200 --> 01:13:55,316
as much as I loved you.

899
01:14:33,480 --> 01:14:34,833
Ooh.

900
01:14:43,040 --> 01:14:45,952
Surprise, surprise.

901
01:14:46,080 --> 01:14:49,038
Professor Brainard.
Dr Reynolds.

902
01:14:49,120 --> 01:14:51,759
Good evening. Sit down.

903
01:14:54,400 --> 01:14:56,470
You look, uh--

904
01:14:56,600 --> 01:15:00,388
- Weary.
- Yes. Weary.

905
01:15:00,480 --> 01:15:02,596
You came to repay your loan?

906
01:15:02,720 --> 01:15:07,157
- No.
- I know you didn`t. I was
just having a little fun.

907
01:15:07,240 --> 01:15:09,435
I`m here to sell you
the flubber.

908
01:15:09,560 --> 01:15:12,199
You been to your house recently?

909
01:15:12,320 --> 01:15:15,915
- Yes.
- Do I really need to buy it?

910
01:15:17,520 --> 01:15:19,636
Flubber`s
a very quixotic substance.

911
01:15:19,760 --> 01:15:23,958
It`s very difficult to handle.
Have you tried to do anything with it?

912
01:15:24,080 --> 01:15:27,709
My man is working on it.
It won`t be a problem.

913
01:15:27,840 --> 01:15:31,594
Well, I could make it
a lot easier for you.

914
01:15:31,680 --> 01:15:34,069
If you give us a 30-day
extension on the loan,

915
01:15:34,200 --> 01:15:36,077
I`ll tell you everything
I know...

916
01:15:36,160 --> 01:15:39,038
and make you
a great deal of flubber.

917
01:15:39,160 --> 01:15:41,151
I`ll give you the 30 days,

918
01:15:41,280 --> 01:15:44,636
and after that
you give me two years.

919
01:15:44,760 --> 01:15:48,116
Whatever you come up with
over the next two years is mine.

920
01:15:48,240 --> 01:15:50,196
That`s not fair!

921
01:15:50,280 --> 01:15:52,714
Shop somewhere else, lady.

922
01:15:52,800 --> 01:15:55,633
Sara, Sara. I`ll do it.

923
01:15:58,840 --> 01:16:04,039
- May I see the flubber?
- Would you like to show these
good people to the library?

924
01:16:43,680 --> 01:16:46,797
You`re going to enjoy this.
Professor?

925
01:16:48,520 --> 01:16:51,159
I got you a little help.

926
01:16:52,920 --> 01:16:58,040
- The lovebirds.
- Wilson. Shame on you.

927
01:16:58,120 --> 01:17:01,590
- Welcome.
- So you finally gave up teaching.

928
01:17:01,720 --> 01:17:06,589
How could I pass up the opportunity
to transform the energy industry?

929
01:17:06,720 --> 01:17:10,235
Flubber. Very interesting, Phil.

930
01:17:10,360 --> 01:17:12,430
Too bad it`s so unstable.

931
01:17:12,560 --> 01:17:16,678
I was just looking over the formula.
Dangerous mix.

932
01:17:16,800 --> 01:17:19,792
You just have to know how to
deal with it, really. It just
takes a few simple precautions--

933
01:17:19,880 --> 01:17:21,836
Hey, hey. Hang on, "Einsteen."

934
01:17:21,920 --> 01:17:24,718
- Stein.
- Whatever.

935
01:17:27,200 --> 01:17:32,399
- What`s this?
- Well, it-it`s a hand cream that
acts as a separating agent.

936
01:17:32,480 --> 01:17:35,313
- Right.
- Um--

937
01:17:37,600 --> 01:17:40,433
It`s so I can handle
the flubber.

938
01:17:40,520 --> 01:17:42,829
- It`s okay.
- Thank you.

939
01:17:42,920 --> 01:17:47,232
She needs to assist me.
Rub it on your hands.

940
01:17:54,400 --> 01:17:56,550
It`s a, uh--

941
01:17:59,600 --> 01:18:01,636
squirt gun.

942
01:18:01,760 --> 01:18:06,675
- What`s it for?
- I use that to lower
the temperature of the tank.

943
01:18:06,800 --> 01:18:08,597
Let him have it.

944
01:18:11,080 --> 01:18:15,631
No, no. Give it to him.
N-No, no. Give it to him.

945
01:18:15,760 --> 01:18:18,194
W-- Stop that
and give it to him.

946
01:18:19,520 --> 01:18:22,318
Put-Put it in his hand
and give it to him.

947
01:18:22,400 --> 01:18:26,518
No, no, no, no, no.
Give the gun to him.

948
01:18:27,600 --> 01:18:30,068
Oh.

949
01:18:30,200 --> 01:18:32,111
- Thank you.
- You`re welcome.

950
01:18:56,280 --> 01:18:58,999
You okay? lt`s me.

951
01:19:04,280 --> 01:19:07,158
There you go.

952
01:19:07,280 --> 01:19:09,350
Oh. Shh.

953
01:19:16,720 --> 01:19:19,154
Do it for Weebo.

954
01:19:19,280 --> 01:19:21,396
Look out!

955
01:19:24,000 --> 01:19:25,718
Ooh.

956
01:19:31,520 --> 01:19:33,511
Get him!

957
01:19:38,760 --> 01:19:41,513
- Oh, dear.
- Sara? Going somewhere?

958
01:19:41,600 --> 01:19:43,431
Wilson.

959
01:19:45,560 --> 01:19:47,312
Ooh.

960
01:19:53,120 --> 01:19:55,714
Left, left, left,
right, right, left.

961
01:20:00,320 --> 01:20:02,356
- Sara!
- Huh?
- Grab her.

962
01:20:02,480 --> 01:20:04,755
- What?
- Jump!

963
01:20:04,840 --> 01:20:06,751
I`m coming, Sara!

964
01:20:06,880 --> 01:20:08,757
Yo!

965
01:20:16,560 --> 01:20:18,835
Ooh!

966
01:20:23,440 --> 01:20:25,510
Hey, Lumpy. Hmm?

967
01:20:25,600 --> 01:20:27,955
- Come on.
- Let`s go, smart guy.

968
01:20:35,600 --> 01:20:38,672
- Ow.
- Phillip, look out!

969
01:20:49,360 --> 01:20:51,157
Sara!

970
01:20:53,640 --> 01:20:55,915
- Get him.
- This one`s for Weebo.

971
01:21:08,320 --> 01:21:10,117
Ooh.

972
01:21:28,040 --> 01:21:29,871
Oh, Mommy--

973
01:21:42,360 --> 01:21:44,920
Wow.

974
01:21:53,680 --> 01:21:56,069
Oh.

975
01:22:07,680 --> 01:22:09,477
Beautiful.

976
01:22:11,280 --> 01:22:14,238
For as much as these
two people have finally...

977
01:22:14,360 --> 01:22:16,874
consented together
in holy wedlock...

978
01:22:16,960 --> 01:22:21,238
and have witnessed the same
before God and this company,

979
01:22:21,360 --> 01:22:24,557
I pronounce, believe it or not,

980
01:22:24,640 --> 01:22:28,315
that they be
husband and wife together.

981
01:22:28,440 --> 01:22:31,557
- You may now kiss the video screen.
- Oh.

982
01:22:39,600 --> 01:22:41,477
Love you, Sara.

983
01:22:42,800 --> 01:22:44,597
I love you.

984
01:22:48,800 --> 01:22:53,794
I`ll meet you at the reception. I`m
almost done. It`s gonna be remarkable.

985
01:22:53,920 --> 01:22:56,036
Phillip, please be careful.

986
01:22:56,160 --> 01:22:59,596
Don`t worry. These chemicals
are completely compatible.

987
01:22:59,680 --> 01:23:04,037
There`s no chance
that anything could go wrong!

988
01:23:18,880 --> 01:23:23,158
Hey, pal. We`re 30,000 feet
up in the air.

989
01:23:23,240 --> 01:23:26,676
There`s no monsters or bad guys
way up here, okay?

990
01:23:26,800 --> 01:23:29,075
You can look out the window.

991
01:23:46,320 --> 01:23:48,276
Mom. Mom!

992
01:23:48,360 --> 01:23:51,796
Flubber`s gone. Get back here!

993
01:23:56,840 --> 01:23:59,308
When we get to the hotel,
I don`t care what you say,

994
01:23:59,440 --> 01:24:01,556
I`m not sharing a room with him.

995
01:24:01,680 --> 01:24:04,274
Look at him. He`s gross.
He bounces all the time.

996
01:24:04,400 --> 01:24:06,516
He squeaks. He phase-shifts.

997
01:24:06,600 --> 01:24:08,636
I mean, he`s a quasi-plasmoid.

998
01:24:08,760 --> 01:24:10,910
If it`s hot in Hawaii,
I hope he melts.

999
01:24:15,640 --> 01:24:17,551
Ow

